"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The metric function passed to DBSCAN should take two arrays from X as input and return a value indicating the distance between them. However, the get_point_distance function is returning a 2D array instead of a single value, which is incorrect. The euclidean_distances function returns a 2D array of distances between all pairs of points, but in this case, we only need the distance between two points.\",\n  \"patch\": \"26c26\\n< return euclidean_distances([p1.to_list()], [p2.to_list()])\\n---\\n> return euclidean_distances([p1.to_list()], [p2.to_list()])[0][0]\\n\"\n}"